A Lua test suite written with Loon.

--five   [string] no description   
--four   [number] no description  (required) 
--one    [flag] no description (default: on)  
--seven  [anotherA|anotherB] yet another description (default: nil) (required) 
--six    [choiceA|choiceB] no description (default: choiceB)  
--three  [4|5] another description (default: 5)  
--two    [flag] some description (default: off)  

For strings, numbers or choices, supply the argument like this:
  --name argument / --name=argument

For flags, no argument is required to turn the option on.
To turn it off, supply an option of 'false':
  --name false / --name=false
